[{"category":"section","location":"atomic-channel/#AtomicChannel","page":"AtomicChannel","text":"AtomicChannel is a bounded, lock-free, multi-producer multi-consumer channel built on atomic operations.","title":"AtomicChannel"},{"category":"section","location":"atomic-channel/#Create-a-channel","page":"AtomicChannel","text":"using AtomicChannels\n\nchnl = AtomicChannel{Int}(4)\n\nThe channel capacity is fixed. Producers block on put! when full, and consumers block on take! when empty.","title":"Create a channel"},{"category":"section","location":"atomic-channel/#Core-operations","page":"AtomicChannel","text":"put!(chnl, item): blocking push\ntake!(chnl): blocking pop\ntryput!(chnl, item): non-blocking push, returns Bool\ntrytake!(chnl): non-blocking pop, returns item or nothing","title":"Core operations"},{"category":"section","location":"atomic-channel/#Example","page":"AtomicChannel","text":"chnl = AtomicChannel{Int}(2)\n\nput!(chnl, 10)\nput!(chnl, 20)\n\nok = tryput!(chnl, 30)  # false, channel is full\nx = take!(chnl)         # 10\ny = trytake!(chnl)      # 20\nz = trytake!(chnl)      # nothing","title":"Example"},{"category":"section","location":"atomic-channel/#Compatibility-helpers","page":"AtomicChannel","text":"AtomicChannel implements common Base channel-style utilities:\n\nOther non-blocking operations:\nempty!(::AtomiChannel)\niterations like for loop, collect, etc.\nWaiting and peeking:\nwait(::AtomicChannel)\nfetch(::AtomicChannel): wait and peek the next item but not take it away from AtomicChannel.\nState and capacity:\nisready(::AtomicChannel)\nisempty(::AtomicChannel)\nisfull(::AtomicChannel)\nlength(::AtomicChannel)\nChannel compatibility:\nisopen(::AtomicChannel) = true\nclose(::AtomicChannel) = nothing, etc","title":"Compatibility helpers"},{"category":"section","location":"atomic-channel/#Notes","page":"AtomicChannel","text":"trytake! uses nothing to mean \"empty\". If item can be nothing, prefer blocking take! when ambiguity matters.\nInternal ring indices are periodically wrapped to avoid long-running counter growth.","title":"Notes"},{"category":"section","location":"api/#API-Reference","page":"API Reference","text":"","title":"API Reference"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#AtomicChannels.AtomicCell","page":"API Reference","text":"mutable struct AtomicCell{T}\n    state::Threads.Atomic{UInt8}\n    value::Base.RefValue{Union{T, Nothing}}\nend\n\nA cell in the AtomicChannel. The state can be empty (0), filled (1), or busy (2; being written/cleared). The value field holds the item when the cell is filled or nothing when it is empty.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"AtomicChannels.AtomicCell"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#AtomicChannels.AtomicChannel","page":"API Reference","text":"AtomicChannel{T<:Any}(capacity::Int)\nAtomicChannel(capacity::Int) -> AtomicChannel{Any}\n\nA thread-safe, lock-free and task-free channel/queue implementation for type T. \n\nIt supports concurrent producers and consumers with blocking and non-blocking APIs. The channel is implemented as a ring buffer with atomic operations to ensure thread safety.\n\ncapacity specifies the maximum number of items the channel can hold. It must be greater than 0.\n\nExamples\n\njulia> chnl = AtomicChannel{Int}(2)\nAtomicChannel{Int64} with 0/2 items\n  head = 0, tail = 0, free = 2\n  slots = [..]\n\njulia> put!(chnl, 1)\nAtomicChannel{Int64} with 1/2 items\n  head = 0, tail = 1, free = 1\n  slots = [X.]\n\njulia> put!(chnl, 2)\nAtomicChannel{Int64} with 2/2 items\n  head = 0, tail = 2, free = 0\n  slots = [XX]\n\njulia> tryput!(chnl, 3)  # returns false since the chnl is full\nfalse\n\njulia> take!(chnl)  # returns 1\n1\n\njulia> take!(chnl)  # returns 2\n2\n\njulia> trytake!(chnl)  # returns nothing since the chnl is empty\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"AtomicChannels.AtomicChannel"},{"category":"type","location":"api/#AtomicChannels.ReusePool","page":"API Reference","text":"ReusePool(create::Function, size::Int = 1, reset::Function = identity)\nReusePool{T}(create::Function, size::Int = 1, reset::Function = identity)\n\nA thread-safe and reusable pool of objects of type T. The pool allows for efficient reuse of objects, reducing the overhead of creating and destroying objects frequently. The pool is thread-safe and can be used in concurrent environments.\n\nOnce a ReusePool is created, it comes with one instance of T created by the create function. The pool can hold up to size instances of T. When an item is taken from the pool, it is removed from the pool until it is put back.\n\nFields\n\ncreate::Function: A function that creates a new instance of T. This function must be thread-safe and should return a new instance of T each time it is called.\nreset::Function: A function that resets an instance of T to a clean state. Defaults to identity. This function must edit the item in place and should not return a new instance.\nchnl::AtomicChannel{T}: An atomic lock-free channel that holds the reusable objects.\n\nAPI\n\nBlocking: take!(pool), put!(pool, item)\nNon-blocking: acquire!(pool), release!(pool, item), fill!(pool)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"AtomicChannels.ReusePool"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#AtomicChannels.acquire!-Tuple{ReusePool}","page":"API Reference","text":"acquire!(reuse_pool::ReusePool{T}) where T<:Any\n\nGets an item from the pool without blocking. If the pool is empty, a new item is created using the create function.\n\nSee also: release! to release an item back to the pool without blocking.\n\nSee also: take! and put! for blocking versions.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"AtomicChannels.acquire!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#AtomicChannels.release!-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{ReusePool{T}, T}} where T","page":"API Reference","text":"release!(reuse_pool::ReusePool{T}, item::T) where T<:Any\n\nReleases an item back to the pool without blocking. If the pool is full, the item is discarded. Return true if the item was successfully released back to the pool, or false if the item was discarded because the pool is full.\n\nSee also: acquire! to get an item from the pool without blocking.\n\nSee also: take! and put! for blocking versions.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"AtomicChannels.release!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#AtomicChannels.tryput!-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{AtomicChannel{T}, T}} where T","page":"API Reference","text":"tryput!(chnl::AtomicChannel{T}, item::T) where T<:Any\ntryput!(reset_func::Base.Callable, chnl::AtomicChannel{T}, item::T) where T<:Any\n\nNon-blocking variant of put!.\n\nThe reset_func should in-place edit item. It is applied to the item only when the item can be inserted into the chnl.\n\nReturns true if item was inserted, or false immediately when the chnl is full.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"AtomicChannels.tryput!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#AtomicChannels.trytake!-Union{Tuple{AtomicChannel{T}}, Tuple{T}} where T","page":"API Reference","text":"trytake!(chnl::AtomicChannel{T}) where T<:Any\n\nNon-blocking variant of take!.\n\nReturns an item from the chnl when available, or nothing immediately when the chnl is empty.\n\nEdge case:\n\nIf you put a nothing into the chnl, it will be treated as a valid item and returned.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"AtomicChannels.trytake!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Base.fetch-Union{Tuple{AtomicChannel{T}}, Tuple{T}} where T","page":"API Reference","text":"fetch(chnl::AtomicChannel{T}) where T<:Any\n\nWaits for and returns (without removing) the first available item from the AtomicChannel.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Base.fetch"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Base.fill!-Union{Tuple{ReusePool{T}}, Tuple{T}} where T","page":"API Reference","text":"fill!(reuse_pool::ReusePool{T}) where T<:Any\n\nFills the pool to its maximum size by creating new items using the create function.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Base.fill!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Base.put!-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{AtomicChannel{T}, T}} where T","page":"API Reference","text":"put!(chnl::AtomicChannel{T}, item::T) where T<:Any\n\nPuts an item into the chnl. If the chnl is full, the function is blocked until space is available.\n\nSee also: take! to take an item from the chnl (blocked when empty).\n\nSee also: tryput! and trytake! for non-blocking versions of put and take.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Base.put!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Base.put!-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{ReusePool{T}, T}} where T","page":"API Reference","text":"put!(reuse_pool::ReusePool{T}, item::T) where T<:Any\n\nPuts an item back into the pool after resetting it. If the pool is full, the function is blocked until space is available.\n\nSee also: take! to take an item from the pool (blocked when empty).\n\nSee also: acquire! and release! for non-blocking versions of take and put.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Base.put!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Base.take!-Tuple{ReusePool}","page":"API Reference","text":"take!(reuse_pool::ReusePool{T}) where T<:Any\n\nTakes an item from the pool. If the pool is empty, the function is blocked until an item is available.\n\nSee also: put! to reset and put an item back to the pool (blocked when full).\n\nSee also: acquire! and release! for non-blocking versions of take and put.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Base.take!"},{"category":"method","location":"api/#Base.take!-Union{Tuple{AtomicChannel{T}}, Tuple{T}} where T","page":"API Reference","text":"take!(chnl::AtomicChannel{T}) where T<:Any\n\nTakes an item from the chnl. If the chnl is empty, the function is blocked until an item is available.\n\nEdge case:\n\nIf you put a nothing into the chnl, it will be treated as a valid item and returned.\n\nSee also: put! to put an item into the chnl (blocked when full).\n\nSee also: tryput! and trytake! for non-blocking versions of put and take.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Base.take!"},{"category":"section","location":"reuse-pool/#ReusePool","page":"ReusePool","text":"ReusePool is a lightweight object pool implemented on top of AtomicChannel.\n\nIt is useful when object construction is expensive and objects can be reset and reused safely.","title":"ReusePool"},{"category":"section","location":"reuse-pool/#Create-a-pool","page":"ReusePool","text":"using AtomicChannels\n\ncreate_obj() = Dict{Symbol, Int}(:count => 0)\nreset_obj!(obj) = (obj[:count] = 0; obj)\n\npool = ReusePool(create_obj, 8, reset_obj!)\n\nConstructor arguments:\n\ncreate: creates a new object\nsize: maximum number of retained objects\nreset: in-place reset function used when putting/releasing objects back","title":"Create a pool"},{"category":"section","location":"reuse-pool/#Blocking-API","page":"ReusePool","text":"take!(pool): take an object, blocks when empty\nput!(pool, obj): reset and return an object, blocks when full","title":"Blocking API"},{"category":"section","location":"reuse-pool/#Non-blocking-API","page":"ReusePool","text":"acquire!(pool): take an object if available, otherwise create a new one\nrelease!(pool, obj): try to return an object, returns true on success\nfill!(pool): pre-fill pool to capacity using create","title":"Non-blocking API"},{"category":"section","location":"reuse-pool/#Example","page":"ReusePool","text":"pool = ReusePool(() -> Vector{Int}(undef, 1024), 4, x -> fill!(x, 0))\n\nbuf = acquire!(pool)    # get pooled buffer or create new\nbuf[1] = 42\nok = release!(pool, buf)","title":"Example"},{"category":"section","location":"reuse-pool/#Display","page":"ReusePool","text":"show(pool) prints a compact occupancy summary, for example:\n\nReusePool{Vector{Int64}} with 2/4 items","title":"Display"},{"category":"section","location":"changelog/#Changelog","page":"Changelog","text":"","title":"Changelog"},{"category":"section","location":"changelog/#1.0.0","page":"Changelog","text":"Release.\nChange docs.","title":"1.0.0"},{"category":"section","location":"changelog/#1.0.0-DEV2","page":"Changelog","text":"","title":"1.0.0-DEV2"},{"category":"section","location":"changelog/#Added","page":"Changelog","text":"AtomicChannel and ReusePool documentation pages.\nMPMC benchmark workflow and versioned benchmark reports.\nBenchmark documentation page in Benchmark.\nChangelog page in docs.","title":"Added"},{"category":"section","location":"changelog/#Changed","page":"Changelog","text":"Improved MPMC throughput across Julia versions (1.8 through 1.12) under most tested contention patterns.\nAtomicChannel token acquisition strategy now uses adaptive spin/yield behavior for better cross-version scheduler performance.\nUpdated benchmark summaries in README and docs.","title":"Changed"},{"category":"section","location":"benchmark/#Benchmark","page":"Benchmark","text":"The benchmark compares AtomicChannel with Base.Channel using a multi-producer multi-consumer (MPMC) workload.","title":"Benchmark"},{"category":"section","location":"benchmark/#Method-Summary","page":"Benchmark","text":"Benchmark target: put/take throughput with items=50000\nMetric: speedup is computed as Channel ÷ AtomicChannel (elapsed time in ms).\nScenario groups:\nCase 1: low-capacity contention (capacity=4 or 1)\nCase 2: higher-capacity, lower data contention (capacity=256)\nCase 3: varying worker/task counts (capacity=256)","title":"Method Summary"},{"category":"section","location":"benchmark/#Representative-Results","page":"Benchmark","text":"Representative speedups are shown below from the latest report for each Julia version.\n\nJulia Case 1: 64 threads, 64 workers, cap=4 Case 2: 32 threads, 32 workers, cap=256 Case 3: 32 threads, 256 workers, cap=256\n1.12.6 23.161x 1.644x 12.106x\n1.11.9 12.383x 2.399x 1.811x\n1.10.11 22.519x 2.810x 1.800x\n1.9.4 9.931x 3.556x 1.849x\n1.8.5 2.622x 1.551x 1.737x\n\nNotes:\n\nMost tested scenarios are faster than Base.Channel.\nSome scheduler/contention mixes can still fall below parity.","title":"Representative Results"},{"category":"section","location":"benchmark/#Raw-Reports","page":"Benchmark","text":"Julia 1.12.6\nJulia 1.11.9\nJulia 1.10.11\nJulia 1.9.4\nJulia 1.8.5","title":"Raw Reports"},{"category":"section","location":"benchmark/#Reproduce","page":"Benchmark","text":"Run from repository root:\n\njulia --project benchmark/mpmc.jl\n\nOr pin the Julia version with juliaup:\n\njulia +1.8 --project benchmark/mpmc.jl\njulia +1.9 --project benchmark/mpmc.jl\njulia +1.10 --project benchmark/mpmc.jl\njulia +1.11 --project benchmark/mpmc.jl\njulia +1.12 --project benchmark/mpmc.jl\n\nEach run generates a versioned report in benchmark/.","title":"Reproduce"},{"category":"section","location":"#AtomicChannels","page":"Home","text":"AtomicChannels provides lock-free concurrent data structures for Julia:\n\nAtomicChannel: fast multi-producer multi-consumer (MPMC) channel, implemented as a ring buffer with atomic operations to ensure thread safety\nReusePool: object pool built on top of AtomicChannel","title":"AtomicChannels"},{"category":"section","location":"#Installation","page":"Home","text":"using Pkg\nPkg.add(\"AtomicChannels\")","title":"Installation"},{"category":"section","location":"#Quick-Start","page":"Home","text":"using AtomicChannels\n\nchnl = AtomicChannel{Int}(2)\nput!(chnl, 1)\nput!(chnl, 2)\n\nx = take!(chnl)      # 1\ny = trytake!(chnl)   # 2\nz = trytake!(chnl)   # nothing\n\npool = ReusePool(() -> Vector{Int}(undef, 16), 4, x -> fill!(x, 0))\nbuf = acquire!(pool)\nbuf[1] = 123\nrelease!(pool, buf)","title":"Quick Start"},{"category":"section","location":"#Contents","page":"Home","text":"Benchmark\nAtomicChannel\nReusePool\nAPI Reference\nChangelog\n\n","title":"Contents"}]
